item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Famous for its spectacular mountain peaks and the loyalty and friendliness of its inhabitants (the Sherpas), the Everest region (Khumbu) is one of the most popular destinations for tourists in Nepal. While many of the routes through the mountains are arduous, there are ample places to rest and enjoy a meal along the way. Furthermore, don't worry about getting lost. Just ask a local the way to the next village on your route, and they will direct you. Most Sherpas under the age of fifty can at least understand basic English, and many speak it fluently.
While trekking is possible in this area the whole year round, the best times to visit are from the beginning of March to mid May and from the beginning of September to mid November. The winters are very cold and snow may make it difficult to travel higher than Tengboche, and also lodges may be closed above this altitude. Summers, on the other hand, are wet, and the spectacular peaks are often lost in the clouds. April and early May is a good time to see the hedgerows and trees bursting into bloom, with Rhododendrons, in particular, adding a spectacular splash of colour to the landscape. However, dust from the plains of India during the spring routinely provide less than ideal conditions for clear mountain views. The views are much better after the summer monsoons have cleared the atmosphere of dust, but the days are shorter and cooler.

item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
After what seemed liked a forever spell of long dreary nights and grey skies, a week somewhere hot and sunny was desperately needed. When thinking about winter sun, there are a few options that spring to mind, but one chilly March morning, myself and my partner James found ourselves en route to the capital of the UAE, Abu Dhabi!
We arrived fairly late in the evening but were greeted at the affectionately known ‘Grandad of Abu Dhabi’, the Hilton Hotel on the Corniche Road (it was the first luxury hotel to be built on the Corniche Road before anything else was there in the 1970’s) with a big smile and were shown to our room. We opted for the executive club floor, giving us access to the club lounge which served complimentary breakfast and snacks & drinks all day, with a great view of the beach and out to the marina. A highlight of my day was the two hours of bottomless prosecco with a window seat as the sun went down in front of the hotel… perfect!

item.title: Hike Around Beautiful Mt. Fuji, Japan
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
It’s a common misconception that the mountain to climb in Japan is Mount Fuji. While it is both the most striking and tallest mountain in the Japanese archipelago, I would argue it’s infinitely better to climb a nearby mountain to marvel at the snow-capped beauty, rather than to climb Fuji itself. Luckily, there are several nearby peaks that provide a spectacular vista with Mount Fuji center stage, which I’ll cover below.
Every summer (from July to September), the promise of climbing Mount Fuji to see the sunrise attracts bus load after bus load of visitors. The usual format is to hike up during the evening, optionally staying for a few hours in a cramped 6,500 yen/person hut and doing the final leg in the early hours just in time to catch the iconic first rays of the sun rising over the eastern edge of Japan.

These words are used for any type of journey, e.g. by bus from Nairobi to Mombasa or by ferry from Dar es Salaam to Unguja. Safari entered the English language at the end of the 1850s thanks to Richard Francis Burton, the famous explorer. The Regimental March of the King’s African Rifles was ‘Funga Safari’, literally ‘tie up the March’, or, in other words, pack up equipment ready to march.

item.title: Glacier walk and northern lights
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: On this day tour, we combine two winter highlights, a glacier walk and a search for the spectacular Aurora Borealis for an amazing day out in nature. The grassroots effort continued to expand despite overwhelming odds. Political leaders got on board and Scottsdale residents voted not once but twice in favor of a sales tax increase to raise money to purchase land. The result is the largest urban preserve in the United States, a crown jewel of city planning and a reminder that just a few determined people can make a difference.

Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque Center (SZGMC) offices are located in the west minarets. item.title: Sandstone, the wave rock at North America
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The Wave is a sandstone rock formation located in Arizona, United States, near its northern border with Utah. The formation is situated on the slopes of the Coyote Buttes in the Paria Canyon-Vermilion Cliffs Wilderness of the Colorado Plateau. The area is administered by the Bureau of Land Management (BLM) at the Grand Staircase-Escalante National Monument visitor center in Kanab, Utah.The formation is well-known among hikers and photographers for its colorful, undulating forms and the difficult hike required to reach it. Due to the fragile nature of the formation and the large number of people wishing to visit it, a daily lottery system is used to dispense only ten next-day permits in person at the Kanab visitor center. Additionally, ten online permits for each date are available four months in advance of a planned trip. A map and information about the hike are supplied to those who have obtained permits

Duniya Dekho are escorted group tours designed for like minded Indian passengers, with Indian meals and Indian Tour Managers. The itineraries are carefully planned coach tours with a mix of essential sightseeing and activities.
The hotels used are normally first class hotels ranging in the 3 star to 4 star category. We also provide optional excursions which you can choose to enhance your experience. Please do check your selected itinerary for inclusions and exclusions.

item.title: Tour Around Asia
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Sum up Asia in a paragraph? Good luck. Positively massive by just about every measure, the sole thread that unites this diverse continent is the sheer diversity of experiences it presents to travellers. Arid deserts and towering peaks; secluded temples and bustling markets; tiny villages and sprawling cities; ancient history and cutting-edge modernity; teeming crowds and places so remote you won’t find another human being around for miles—Asia encompasses all this and so, so, so much more. Don’t expect to absorb it all; dive on in and let it seep into your skin.

item.title: Yosemite Valley tour
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Valley Floor Tour is a two-hour tour of Yosemite Valley that operates all year. From approximately April through October, this is an open-air tram tour (weather permitting). From around October through March, this is a bus tour. Glacier Point Tour is a four-hour round-trip tour to Glacier Point and back. (One-way tickets are available.) This tour operates when the Glacier Point Road is open (typically, late May until sometime in November, conditions permitting). Grand Tour is a full-day tour (~ 8 hours) that visits Yosemite Valley, Glacier Point and the Mariposa Grove of Giant Sequoias. This tour operates during the late spring through summer (May - September, conditions permitting). Tuolumne Meadows Tour is an all-day tour to Tuolumne Meadows and back. (One-way tickets are available.) This tour operates from July through early September, conditions permitting.

item.title: it's a jungle out there
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
"It's a jungle out there" is an idiomatic English expression describing a dangerous and threatening situation. It often has the broader implication that the entire world is the proverbial "jungle," a dangerous environment filled with hazards in which all parties are out only for themselves. This expression draws on a long tradition in English idiom and literature of representing the natural world, and jungles in particular, as threatening and chaotic. The term is primarily American, although it also occurs in British English.
The expression is one of a number of English idioms in which the jungle stands for an uncivilized environment, a threatening natural world as opposed to the safety of the cultural world. "The law of the jungle" describes fundamental laws of human interaction, and is often used to describe brutal, unfair laws under which the strong exploit the weak, although ironically this is not consistent with the term's original use in Rudyard Kipling's "The Jungle Book." The term "jungle drums" refers to the informal methods of communication by which information often travels. "The concrete jungle" refers to cities, suggesting that cities are, in their own way, as dangerous and filled with predators as the wilderness.

item.title: Having A Wonderful Time
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Bored New York office girl Teddy goes to a vacation camp in the Catskill Mountains called Camp Kare Free, for rest and to get away from the noisy, busy, city life and avoid advances from Emil. She meets and at first does not like waiter Chick. She also meets friend Fay, her roommate Miriam, and Buzzy. Miriam has eyes for Buzzy, who seems to have eyes for everyone. Within her two-week stay, Teddy and Chick fall in love and spend every day together.
One night Teddy becomes angry with Chick and leaves him to go to a party where she meets up with Buzzy. A storm rolls in and Buzzy invites her to his cabin, which he rents by himself. Initially refusing and wanting to be with friends, Teddy sees Chick at the party and asks Buzzy to go to his cabin. At the cabin she tells Buzzy she isn't interested but loves to play backgammon. Chick rushes in to save Teddy but becomes embarrassed when he sees the innocent board game. He returns to the party and waits there to talk with Teddy when she returns home. Teddy accidentally falls asleep at Buzzy's cabin and stays overnight.
While trying to sneak out the next morning Teddy is spotted leaving by Miriam. Emil shows up to drive Teddy back to the city and the two sit down to eat, with Chick as their waiter. All three of them overhear Miriam yelling at Buzzy for having Teddy stay overnight. Chick goes on a punching spree and chases after Teddy out of the restaurant. The two reconcile and plan their married life.

item.content:encoded: a place or condition of great happiness where everything is exactly as you would like it to be:Paradise ultimately comes from an Iranian word that the Greeks modified into paradeisos, meaning "enclosed park." In Hellenistic Greek, "paradeisos" was also used in the Septuagint - an early Greek translation of Jewish scriptures - in reference to the Garden of Eden. Early Christian writers also used "paradeisos" for both Heaven and for the place where righteous souls await resurrection. These senses of "paradeisos" entered into Late Latin as paradisus, and then into Anglo-French (and later, Middle English) as "paradis." Though originally used in theological senses in English, "paradise" has also come to refer to more earthly states and places of delight as well.

item.title: Tour Around Asia
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Sum up Asia in a paragraph? Good luck. Positively massive by just about every measure, the sole thread that unites this diverse continent is the sheer diversity of experiences it presents to travellers. Arid deserts and towering peaks; secluded temples and bustling markets; tiny villages and sprawling cities; ancient history and cutting-edge modernity; teeming crowds and places so remote you won’t find another human being around for miles—Asia encompasses all this and so, so, so much more. item.content:encoded: Valley Floor Tour is a two-hour tour of Yosemite Valley that operates all year. From approximately April through October, this is an open-air tram tour (weather permitting). This tour operates when the Glacier Point Road is open (typically, late May until sometime in November, conditions permitting). Grand Tour is a full-day tour (~ 8 hours) that visits Yosemite Valley, Glacier Point and the Mariposa Grove of Giant Sequoias. This tour operates during the late spring through summer (May - September, conditions permitting). Tuolumne Meadows Tour is an all-day tour to Tuolumne Meadows and back. item.title: Best Time to Go
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Between October and December is the best time to visit Nepal as the skies are generally clear and the views spectacular. The weather remains dry until about April. January and February can be very cold, especially at night, but will reward you with incredible panoramas and quieter trekking trails as there are fewer visitors. Late spring is a beautiful time to travel as the rhododendrons burst into bloom. From May, heat and humidity levels build until the monsoon rains arrive in June and the clouds obscure the glorious mountain views. Nepal celebrates festivals all year, so there is often a festival or pilgrimage taking place - ask your specialist for more details as the dates often change from year to year.

item.title: Getting There
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Travel dates back to antiquity where wealthy Greeks and Romans would travel for leisure to their summer homes and villas in cities such as Pompeii and Baiae. While early travel tended to be slower, more dangerous, and more dominated by trade and migration, cultural and technological advances over many years have tended to mean that travel has become easier and more accessible. Mankind has come a long way in transportation since Christopher Columbus sailed to the new world from Spain in 1492, an expedition which took over 10 weeks to arrive at the final destination; to the 21st century where aircraft allow travel from Spain to the United States overnight.

The Australian Government has Reciprocal Health Care Agreements with the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland, New Zealand, Sweden, the Netherlands, Finland, Belgium, Norway, Slovenia, Malta and Italy, which entitle travellers to some subsidised health services. It is best to check your eligibility before you leave home and have appropriate travel insurance to cover your stay in Australia.

Birgunj

Birgunj is one of the trading hubs in the southern plain Terai of Nepal and is located in Parsa district. Birgunj is a major city of Province No. 2 and it borders with Raxual (an Indian City of Bihar State) to the South. This city is the second largest city in the Terai region of Nepal after Biratnagar. It was declared as a metropolitan city in 2017 along with Biratnagar. While entering Nepal from Patna and Kolkata, Birgunj is commonly called the “Gateway to Nepal”.  

Birgunj Metropolitan City

Birgunj metropolitan city is the sixth most populated metropolitan city of Nepal. The total area of the city is 75.24 Sq. KM i.e. 29.05 Sq. Miles. According to the census conducted in 2011, the total population of this metropolitan city is 204,816. Mr. Vijay Sarawagi is the mayor of Birgunj Metropolitan city and Ms. Shanti Karki is the deputy mayor.  

Birgunj Map

Birgunj Weather

Like in Biratnagar, Birgunj has a warm and temperate climate. As with most places in Nepal, Birgunj witnesses much more rainfall in summer than in winter. Annually Birgunj receives rainfall in an average of 349 mm. With an average of 349 mm, the month of July receives the highest amount of rainfall during the year and December is the driest month of all. The precipitation during this month is somewhere around 3 mm. The annual average temperature of Birgunj is 24.7 degree Celsius. January is the coldest month with the average temperature of 15.8 degree Celsius and the May is the warmest month. The average temperature during the month is 30.2 degree Celsius. The variation in temperature is 14.4 degree Celsius whereas the difference in precipitation is 346 mm.

Consulate General of India, Birgunj (India in Nepal)

The Consulate General of India, Birgunj is located in Shreepur and it was established in 2004. The consulate undertakes the activities related to mutual cooperation and cultural exchange in order to expand the friendship between the two countries and people. Contact Information: Consulate General of India, Birgunj (India in Nepal) Shreepur, Birgunj, 44300 Emergency 24*7 Phone number: +977-9855036213 Phone Number: +977-51-532264 Email: hoc.birgunj@mea.gov.in Website: http://www.cgibirgunj.gov.in    

Journalism and News in Birgunj

Prateek Daily

Prateek daily is one of the most reputed newspaper dailies in Birgunj, Nepal. This daily newspaper is the only “A” graded national daily published in Province No. 2. Mr. Jagadish Prasad Sharma is the chief editor of this news daily and Bikash Sharma is the Editor/Manager of the daily. Similarly, Prateek Publication Group Pvt. Ltd is the publisher of this news and is located in Birgunj-14. Contact Information; Prateek Publication Pvt. Ltd, Trimurti Cinema Hall Road, Shreepur, Birgunj-14 Post Box number: 79 Phone Number: +977-51-525122/523105 Email: prateekdainik@yahoo.com, prateekdaily@gmail.com

Radio Birgunj

Radio Birgunj is famous for being the first and foremost radio from Japan operated by Nepali people with coordination of center for Business limited Japan. Dhruv Sah is the chairman and managing director of the radio. The frequency of Radio Birgunj is 99 MHz. Contact Information: Radio Birgunj, Murli Bagaicha-15, Birgunj, Nepal Email: radiobirgunj99mhzfm@gmail.com Website: http://www.radiobirgunj.com Phone: +977–051-528299, 525099, 528699

Transportation

Birgunj to Kathmandu

The distance between Birgunj and Kathmandu is 135.8 KM via Kulekhani-Sisneri- Pharping road. However, the actual distance from Birgunj to Kathmandu through the bus route is about 275 KM. There are regular buses traveling to Kathmandu from Birgunj. The bus fare is around Rs. 400-Rs. 500 i.e. $4- $5 per person for a normal bus. The deluxe buses (with the facilities of Wi-fi) charge more fare which around Rs. 1100 ($11) and they’re comparatively luxurious than the normal ones. Travel duration is about 10 hours until the bus reaches Kathmandu. However, if you prefer to travel to Kathmandu from Birgunj through the shorter route mentioned above, you have to either hire a car or taxi. It’s going to take you somewhere between 5-6 hours of time until you reach Kathmandu. Similarly, since Birgunj doesn’t have an airport on its own, there are regular flights from Simara to Kathmandu. The flight duration is less than 20 minutes and there are regular flights from Budhha air (around 6 flights daily). Simara is just 20 KM away from Birgunj via Tribhuvan Highway. Many people also have queries regarding the availability of Train from Birgunj to Kathmandu. Unfortunately, the capital city is not linked with railway stations in any way; mainly because of the difficult topography.

Birgunj to Pokhara

Pokhara is about 257.3 KM away from Birgunj and it takes around 7-8 hours to reach there by private vehicles. There is a number of tourist buses and also the normal buses go to Pokhara from Birgunj on a regular basis. However, there are no flight options from Birgunj to Pokhara.

Birgunj to Biratnagar

It takes around 6-7 hours from Birgunj to reach Biratnagar through East-West Highway and the distance between these two cities is about 310 KM.

Raxual to Birgunj

Birgunj (central city) is just 10 KM away from Raxual (the Indian trading city) and it takes about half an hour to reach there.

Patna to Birgunj

The distance between Patna and Birgunj is about 225km. Bus duration to reach Patna from Birgunj is somewhere around 6 hours.

Health Services and Facilities

National medical college, Birgunj

National Medical College was established in 2001, promoted by the “National Medical College Company Pvt. Ltd”. This college is one of the best medical colleges in Nepal in terms of infrastructure, academic facilities, and modern sophisticated medical equipment. Following are the courses offered in Nepal Medical College, Birgunj:
  • Bachelor of medicine and bachelor of surgery (MBBS)
  • Postgraduate medical program (M.D., M.S.)
  • Nursing programs: Proficiency Certificate Level (PCL) Nursing, Bachelor of Science (B.Sc.) in Nursing, Bachelor of Nursing (B.N.), Master in Nursing (M.N.).

Delhi Public School (DPS) Birgunj

Delhi Public School (DPS) is one of the reputed educational institutions in central Terai of Nepal. Delhi Public School is run under the management of CG Education and was established in the year 2004. There are students majorly from Nepal and hundreds of students from India as well. Birgunj Institute of Technology

Birgunj Institute of Technology (abbreviated as BIT) was established in 2000 as a private technical institute. BIT is affiliated to the Council for Technical Education and Vocational Training (CTEVT) and so recognized by the Government of Nepal. Following are the courses offered in BIT:
  • Diploma in Civil Engineering (CTEVT): 48
  • Diploma in Mechanical Engineering (CTEVT): 48
  • Diploma in Electrical Engineering (CTEVT): 48
  • Diploma in Computer Engineering (CTEVT): 48
  • Diploma in Mechanical Engineering (CTEVT): 48
Contact Information: Birgunj Institute of Technology (BIT), Pipra-19, Birgunj, Parsa, Nepal Phone: 051- 528020 Email: info@bit.edu.np

Birgunj Public College

Birgunj Public college (BPC in short form) is a complete management college with dual affiliation. The courses; Bachelor of Business Studies (BBS) and Master of Business Studies (MBS) under the affiliation of Tribhuvan University and courses while Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) and Masters of Business Administration (MBA) under the affiliation of Purbanchal University. It is located in Panitanki, Birgunj. Contact Information: Birgunj Public College Institute of Management, Panitanki, Birgunj, Nepal Phone: 051- 523485 Email: bpc.brj@gmail.com

Hotels in Birgunj

Since Birgunj is a trading hub bordering with Raxual in India, there is the increasing number of hotels for travelers as well as for the traders to accommodate during their stay in the city. Among the numerous hotels, India Hotel Makalu, Hotel Suraj, Hotel Vishuwa is some of the popular ones as per the travelers’ review.

Places to visit in Birgunj

Birgunj even though being the commercial hub of central Terai, it is an equally important destination for the touristic attractions. Some of them are mentioned below:
  • Shree Gahawamai Temple (a holy temple for the Hindus)
  • Ghadiarwa Pokhari (a neat and clean pond; a perfect destination for chilling out)
  • Surya Temple (lies in the middle of Ghadiarwa Pokhari and the temple is dedicated to the Sun God)
  • Parsa Wildlife Reserve (a protected area for endangered wild animals and plants)
  • Gadimai Temple (a temple dedicated to the goddess of power. A popular festival called Gadhimai festival held for a month-long duration is held in this temple)
  • Ghantaghar (situated in the middle of Birgunj is a structure that has been an identity of the city)
